  "event_preview": "Thompson Speedway Motorsports Park is a 0.625-mile (1.006 km) asphalt oval in Thompson, Connecticut — the first paved oval in American motorsport history, built in 1940 and still racing. No track has hosted more NASCAR Whelen Modified Tour events than Thompson, which will welcome the series for the 159th time Sunday for the Icebreaker 150. The high-banked, fast layout produces some of the quickest lap times in Modified Tour competition and rewards track position above almost everything else — passing is possible but difficult, making qualifying order and pit strategy the defining factors in most races here. The event is also the opener for the 2026 FloRacing Connecticut Challenge, a four-race miniseries exclusive to events at Thompson and Stafford Speedway, with $25,000 in overall prize money.\n\nJustin Bonsignore holds the all-time Modified Tour wins record at Thompson with 14 victories, one shy of Mike Stefanik's all-time record of 15. A win Sunday would tie him with the series legend. The all-time qualifying lap record at Thompson belongs to Justin Bonsignore, who turned a 19.039-second lap in 2024 Icebreaker qualifying to claim pole position.",
